AB  - It is argued that, in most cases, model selection procedures, including those based on popular criteria such as predictive loss and information, lead to inadmissible procedures. In particular, properties of the Akaike Information Criterion (AIC) in a nested sequence of regression models are analyzed by reduction to an appropriate canonical form. It is shown that the AIC has some undesirable features, and an alternative proper Bayes procedure is suggested. Numerical compari- sons of risks are presented.
