AB  - We examine some interpretations and theoretical properties of the ridge regression estimators. As such we (i) interpret the GRR estimator as an OLS one based on transformed explanatory variables; (ii) compare the GRR and OLS estimators using the confidence regions; (iii) prove the optimality of the OLS estimator for estimating the signs of the parameters;and (iv) compare the necessary and sufficient condition for the transformed explanatory variables to be less collinear than the initial ones with the condition for improving the OLS estimator.
