AB  - In this paper we develop small-σ and large-T asymptotic expansions of the distribution functions of a family of adaptive shrinkage estimators and theirF-ratios. We demonstrate that the small-σ approximation is much more accurate than the large-T approximation. The small-σ approximate distribution function of the improvedF-ratio is a weighted sum of centralF distribution functions with varying degrees of freedom. This result is useful for forming confidence intervals and testing hypotheses using shrinkage estimators.
